    "note": "Approved. 56 vocab + 48 grammar (the bank has 56 rows, not the 55 the brief stated — the gen agent caught it) across two structures: one/ones (substitute pronoun) and some/any (quantity), 12 formats each. No grants needed (one/ones/some/any are allowlist). Notably ZERO glosses — the vocab agent rephrased every definition into taught-only words (a heavily food/restaurant unit). Smoke-check fixed 4 bank-match mismatches (tomato/potato/glasses plural annotations, to-drop's de), the straightaway \"straight away\" variant (→ partial), and a V-14 false positive on the legit compound Schoko+eis (→ Schokoladeneis). Verify round 1: removed a true-synonym distractor (customer for consumer) and a superordinate (machine for crane), fixed a drink/food reply mismatch (mt apple-juice ↔ I love it), added a missing translation variant, and reworded all 4 anagram cues off German grammar terms (Nomen/Plural/Mengenangabe/Verneinung); round 2 clean. some/any precision (some=affirmative/offer, any=question/negative) keyed correctly throughout. 60 translations adjudicated (Austrian food regionalisms — Zwetschken/Erdäpfel/Paradeiser — correctly partial). rejectRate 0.0%."
